---
import MarketingLayout from "../../components/marketing/MarketingLayout.astro";

const title = "FraiseQL for Developers";
const description = "Build faster APIs with less complexity. Write SQL, map to types, serve GraphQL. No resolvers. No N+1.";
---

<MarketingLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="audience-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>For Developers</h1>
      <p>Build APIs the way you think about data</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="audience-content">
    <div class="container">

      <section class="intro-section">
        <h2>Your Problem</h2>
        <p>You're tired of:</p>
        <ul class="problem-list">
          <li>Writing field resolvers for every relationship</li>
          <li>Fighting N+1 queries with DataLoaders</li>
          <li>Debugging why a simple query runs 50 database hits</li>
          <li>Spending more time optimizing than building features</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You know SQL. You understand your database. You just want to serve it as GraphQL.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="value-section">
        <h2>What FraiseQL Gives You</h2>

        <div class="value-card">
          <h3>✅ Think in SQL</h3>
          <p>Write SQL views. Compose JSONB. You understand exactly what's happening.</p>
          <p>No magic. No ORM generating queries you didn't ask for.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="value-card">
          <h3>✅ Map to Types</h3>
          <p>Define types in your language. FraiseQL validates that types match views.</p>
          <pre><code set:html={`# Your schema matches your database
from uuid import UUID

@fraiseql.type
class User:
  id: UUID
  name: str
  email: str`}></code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="value-card">
          <h3>✅ No Field Resolvers</h3>
          <p>No per-field queries. No N+1 prevention logic. Just queries and mutations.</p>
          <pre><code set:html={`# One query. One database hit. Done.
@fraiseql.query(sql_source="v_user")
def user(id: UUID) -> User:
  pass`}></code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="value-card">
          <h3>✅ Deploy with Confidence</h3>
          <p>Views compile at deploy time. Errors caught before production.</p>
          <p>No runtime schema interpretation. Just execute.</p>
        </div>

      </section>

      <section class="comparison-section">
        <h2>How FraiseQL vs Traditional GraphQL</h2>

        <div class="comparison-item">
          <h3>❌ Traditional GraphQL</h3>
          <pre><code set:html={`# Fetch user
@resolver
async def user(info, id) -> User:
  return db.find_user(id)

# Fetch user + posts (needs resolver)
@resolver
async def posts(parent, info) -> List[Post]:
  posts = db.find_posts(parent.id)  # Separate query!
  return posts

# Result: N+1 problem
# 1 user query + 1 posts query per user = 1 + N queries`}></code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="comparison-item">
          <h3>✅ FraiseQL</h3>
          <pre><code set:html={`# SQL view pre-composes everything
CREATE VIEW v_user_with_posts AS
SELECT id, jsonb_build_object(
  'name', name,
  'posts', (SELECT jsonb_agg(...))
) AS data
FROM tb_user;

# Single resolver
@fraiseql.query(sql_source="v_user_with_posts")
def user(id: UUID) -> User:
  pass

# Result: 1 query for user + posts`}></code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="learning-section">
        <h2>Your Learning Path</h2>

        <div class="path-step">
          <div class="step-number">1</div>
          <h3>Start: 10 minutes</h3>
          <p>Read the Getting Started guide. Write your first view and schema.</p>
          <a href="/docs/getting-started/quickstart/" class="link">Get Started →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="path-step">
          <div class="step-number">2</div>
          <h3>Understand: 20 minutes</h3>
          <p>Learn how FraiseQL works under the hood and why it's different.</p>
          <a href="/how-it-works/" class="link">How It Works →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="path-step">
          <div class="step-number">3</div>
          <h3>Think: 30 minutes</h3>
          <p>Explore the philosophy. Why database-first? Why CQRS? Why compilation?</p>
          <a href="/docs/concepts/how-it-works/" class="link">Philosophy →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="path-step">
          <div class="step-number">4</div>
          <h3>Build: 1-2 hours</h3>
          <p>Create your first real project. Start simple, add complexity.</p>
          <a href="/examples/" class="link">See Examples →</a>
        </div>

      </section>

      <section class="use-case-section">
        <h2>What You Can Build</h2>

        <div class="use-case-grid">
          <div class="use-case-item">
            <h4>REST → GraphQL Migration</h4>
            <p>Have a REST API? Add GraphQL without rewriting everything.</p>
            <p>Define views for existing tables. Map to types. Done.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="use-case-item">
            <h4>Dashboards & Analytics</h4>
            <p>Complex queries with multiple tables? Pre-compose in views.</p>
            <p>Serve aggregations as GraphQL.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="use-case-item">
            <h4>Real-time APIs</h4>
            <p>Use subscriptions on top of pre-composed views.</p>
            <p>Performance scales naturally.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="use-case-item">
            <h4>Multi-tenant SaaS</h4>
            <p>Filter at database level with views.</p>
            <p>Security and performance in one place.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="use-case-item">
            <h4>Mobile Backends</h4>
            <p>Mobile apps need efficient APIs. FraiseQL delivers.</p>
            <p>One query per request. Minimal bandwidth.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="use-case-item">
            <h4>Complex Relationships</h4>
            <p>Posts with comments, likes, author info?</p>
            <p>Compose once in views. Query once from API.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="sdk-section">
        <h2>Choose Your Language</h2>

        <div class="sdk-grid">
          <div class="sdk-card">
            <h3>Python</h3>
            <p>Most popular for data work</p>
            <pre><code set:html={`@fraiseql.query(sql_source="v_users")
def users(limit: int = 100) -> list[User]:
  pass`}></code></pre>
          </div>

          <div class="sdk-card">
            <h3>TypeScript</h3>
            <p>Full type safety in Node</p>
            <pre><code set:html={`@fraiseqlQuery({ sqlSource: "v_users" })
function users(limit: number = 100): User[] {
  // authoring only
}`}></code></pre>
          </div>

          <div class="sdk-card">
            <h3>Go</h3>
            <p>Performance and simplicity</p>
            <pre><code set:html={`func (r *Query) Users(ctx context.Context) ([]*User, error) {
  // authoring only
}`}></code></pre>
          </div>

          <div class="sdk-card">
            <h3>PHP</h3>
            <p>For existing PHP backends</p>
            <pre><code set:html={`#[FraiseQLQuery(sqlSource: "v_users")]
function users(int $limit = 100): array {
  // authoring only
}`}></code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="tools-section">
        <h2>Works With Your Stack</h2>

        <div class="tools-list">
          <div class="tool-group">
            <h4>Databases</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>PostgreSQL</li>
              <li>MySQL / MariaDB</li>
              <li>SQLite</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="tool-group">
            <h4>Authentication</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Auth0</li>
              <li>Firebase</li>
              <li>Clerk</li>
              <li>Custom JWT</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="tool-group">
            <h4>Caching</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Redis</li>
              <li>Memcached</li>
              <li>In-memory</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="tool-group">
            <h4>Deployment</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Docker</li>
              <li>Kubernetes</li>
              <li>Railway</li>
              <li>Fly.io</li>
              <li>AWS</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="common-questions">
        <h2>Common Questions</h2>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>Q: How long to learn?</h4>
          <p><strong>A:</strong> 10-30 minutes to understand. 1-2 hours to build something real. You already know SQL and your language.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>Q: Can I use existing databases?</h4>
          <p><strong>A:</strong> Yes! Add views to your existing schema. No migration needed.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>Q: What about complex logic?</h4>
          <p><strong>A:</strong> Compose data in views. Implement logic in SQL functions (<code>fn_*</code>) that back your mutations — the database is where the logic lives.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>Q: How do I debug?</h4>
          <p><strong>A:</strong> Views are SQL. Run EXPLAIN ANALYZE to see query plans. One query per request means clear debugging.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>Q: Is it production-ready?</h4>
          <p><strong>A:</strong> Yes. Used in production at several companies. Compile-time validation means fewer bugs.</p>
        </div>

      </section>

      <section class="next-section">
        <h2>Ready to Start?</h2>
        <div class="cta-buttons">
          <a href="/docs/getting-started/quickstart/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started Now</a>
          <a href="/examples/" class="btn btn-secondary">See Examples</a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </section>

</MarketingLayout>

<style>
  .audience-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .audience-hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .audience-hero p {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    opacity: 0.9;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 1024px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }

  .audience-content {
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
  }

  .audience-content section {
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .audience-content h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: #1a202c;
  }

  .audience-content h3 {
    color: #1a202c;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .audience-content p {
    color: #4a5568;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  /* Lists */
  .problem-list,
  .tools-list {
    color: #4a5568;
    line-height: 2;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .problem-list li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  /* Value cards */
  .value-card {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .value-card pre {
    background: #f7fafc;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin: 1rem 0 0 0;
  }

  .value-card code {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    color: #2d3748;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Comparison */
  .comparison-item {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .comparison-item pre {
    background: #f7fafc;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    margin: 1rem 0 0 0;
  }

  .comparison-item code {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    color: #2d3748;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  /* Learning path */
  .path-step {
    background: white;
    border-left: 4px solid #667eea;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .step-number {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    background: #667eea;
    color: white;
    border-radius: 50%;
    font-weight: 700;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .path-step h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .path-step p {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
  }

  .link {
    color: #667eea;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .link:hover {
    color: #764ba2;
  }

  /* Use case grid */
  .use-case-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .use-case-item {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .use-case-item h4 {
    margin-top: 0;
    color: #667eea;
  }

  .use-case-item p {
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  /* SDK grid */
  .sdk-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .sdk-card {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .sdk-card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .sdk-card p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .sdk-card pre {
    background: #f7fafc;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    padding: 0.75rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    margin: 0;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .sdk-card code {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    color: #2d3748;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  /* Tools */
  .tools-list {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .tool-group {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .tool-group h4 {
    margin-top: 0;
    color: #667eea;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .tool-group ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .tool-group li {
    padding: 0.25rem 0;
    color: #4a5568;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-item {
    background: white;
    border-left: 4px solid #667eea;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .faq-item h4 {
    margin-top: 0;
    color: #1a202c;
  }

  .faq-item p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .cta-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .btn {
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-block;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
    color: white;
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.3);
  }

  .btn-secondary {
    background: white;
    color: #667eea;
    border: 2px solid #667eea;
  }

  .btn-secondary:hover {
    background: #f7fafc;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .audience-hero h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .path-step {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .cta-buttons {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .btn {
      width: 100%;
      text-align: center;
    }
  }
</style>
